column5: This small 1 lbs brook trout..........  had 11 minnows in him....   he was puking EVERYWERE.  yet still hit my lure .....
He must have heard the old saying "get it while the gettin's good"   What a slob!!!

When Brookies decide to eat, they can really gorge themselves. I've only cleaned a few in the past decade but I remember cleaning an 18" fish once that had 28 minnows in it's stomach, mostly Sticklebacks. It hit a Rapala. A friend once caught one with 13 Smelts in it's belly. Just incredible!!
You was holding out on me eh I wish they'd gorge themselves were I was Beauty pic Kev    as always Jacques

a lady friend of mine once caught a 3 pound speck with 24 assorted size crayfish in it's mouth and belly.  i've also seen mayfly hatches where the fish were regurgitating balls of hexagenia's all over the place.
Chunker for sure !!!  Me and that fish are alot alike but it's potato chips for me.
That's really cool. That trout sure has a healthy appetite!

The brookies up north here are still deep and not eating,waters still freezing.Another week and the big boys will be in the shallows feedin' up a storm.Only caught one brookie this year,a chunky four pounder with a perch half way swallowed!

I'll say.  I once caught a spec with 3 frogs and a baby mouse in it's stomach.  You know that scene in Jaws where they slit open the sharks belly and all kinds of weird crap spills out including a license plate?  That's what it was like when I put the knife to it.  They definitely strap on the feed bag now and again.
Wow...gluttony right there.  i'd have a minnow trap in there like a shot! ( if its legal there of course  )
